1
00:00:00,250 --> 00:00:01,850
(Previously)
I know my son well.

2
00:00:02,230 --> 00:00:03,800
When he loves someone,

3
00:00:03,960 --> 00:00:05,600
he goes all in

4
00:00:05,740 --> 00:00:09,000
without caring about
the consequences for himself.

5
00:00:09,760 --> 00:00:10,390
Q!

6
00:00:11,290 --> 00:00:12,000
Q!

7
00:00:12,100 --> 00:00:14,540
Q doesn't love himself enough to love someone else.

8
00:00:15,050 --> 00:00:17,500
Let's do this for Q's safety.

9
00:00:18,050 --> 00:00:20,910
Before we lose everything
and are both left with nothing,

10
00:00:21,210 --> 00:00:22,140
let go of my hands.

11
00:00:35,360 --> 00:00:36,450
Min, where are you?

12
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:38,210
Why did you run away from me?

13
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:44,268
I guess it must be raining heavily in Bangkok.

14
00:00:48,380 --> 00:00:49,000
Min,

15
00:00:50,330 --> 00:00:51,908
why did we have to move to Chonburi?

16
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:46,510
<i>Min,</i>

17
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:48,660
<i>where are you?</i>

18
00:01:51,780 --> 00:01:53,060
Why did you run away from me?

19
00:01:56,270 --> 00:01:57,730
<i>Can you not do this, Min?</i>

20
00:02:21,288 --> 00:02:22,700
You know what?

21
00:02:25,240 --> 00:02:26,407
I never trusted everything you said.

22
00:02:31,320 --> 00:02:32,600
Stop doing this already.

23
00:02:35,250 --> 00:02:36,360
<i>I really hate you</i>

24
00:02:38,120 --> 00:02:39,410
<i>for leaving me like this.</i>

25
00:02:43,310 --> 00:02:44,400
<i>Can you come back already?</i>

26
00:02:49,890 --> 00:02:52,300
I don't want to live alone again, Min.

27
00:02:56,610 --> 00:02:57,720
I can't.

28
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:39,970
<b>EP08 Decision to Leave</b>

29
00:05:04,360 --> 00:05:07,060
I heard Miss Yada is planning to flee overseas.

30
00:05:07,200 --> 00:05:08,960
Someone saw her at the border.

31
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:12,110
I think she'll hide there until the case cools down.

32
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:14,770
Please send the information you got to my team.

33
00:05:14,960 --> 00:05:15,560
Yes.

34
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:18,770
Q.

35
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:21,300
Why haven't you flown to Vancouver yet?

36
00:05:21,330 --> 00:05:22,100
I'm not going anymore.

37
00:05:22,370 --> 00:05:23,600
But if you feel uneasy

38
00:05:23,660 --> 00:05:25,550
and want to have your men guard me, go ahead.

39
00:05:26,960 --> 00:05:27,500
Q.

40
00:05:27,740 --> 00:05:28,260
Q.

41
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:32,560
Suea.

42
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:34,760
You have some free time these days, right?

43
00:05:35,180 --> 00:05:36,010
Yes, Mr.Kacha.

44
00:05:38,140 --> 00:05:40,150
Did Min tell you where he went?

45
00:05:40,250 --> 00:05:41,620
Come on, Q.

46
00:05:41,650 --> 00:05:43,400
I told you I really have no idea.

47
00:05:43,530 --> 00:05:45,020
I'm still feeling slighted, you know.

48
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:47,110
I see him as my brother,

49
00:05:47,250 --> 00:05:48,250
but look at what he did.

50
00:05:48,330 --> 00:05:49,930
He disappeared without saying a single word to me.

51
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:53,000
James, can you guess where he might have gone?

52
00:05:54,270 --> 00:05:55,400
I can't,

53
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:57,310
but I can guess that

54
00:05:57,840 --> 00:06:00,600
he ran away because of Mhen.

55
00:06:01,630 --> 00:06:02,800
For someone like Min,

56
00:06:03,410 --> 00:06:04,400
if it's about his brother,

57
00:06:05,020 --> 00:06:05,950
he can leave everything behind.

58
00:06:08,140 --> 00:06:10,500
I think you should get over him,

59
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:13,110
He's thought it through enough.

60
00:06:30,020 --> 00:06:30,620
Min.

61
00:06:37,350 --> 00:06:37,970
Min.

62
00:06:55,550 --> 00:06:58,460
<i>Promise me you won't let go of my hands, Min.</i>

63
00:06:59,030 --> 00:06:59,860
<i>I promise.</i>

64
00:07:06,570 --> 00:07:08,540
I have three more exams to go.

65
00:07:08,700 --> 00:07:10,620
How could I finish studying in time?

66
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:11,340
<i>Don't worry, Jeen.</i>

67
00:07:11,350 --> 00:07:12,310
<i>I'll tutor you as always,</i>

68
00:07:12,460 --> 00:07:13,190
<i>but let's make it online this time.</i>

69
00:07:13,250 --> 00:07:13,900
Come on.

70
00:07:13,930 --> 00:07:14,550
Jeen!

71
00:07:15,142 --> 00:07:15,650
<i>Jeen?</i>

72
00:07:15,960 --> 00:07:16,920
<i>Jeen, are you alright?</i>

73
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:17,660
<i>Jeen!</i>

74
00:07:18,970 --> 00:07:19,820
Who are you talking to, Jeen?

75
00:07:28,840 --> 00:07:30,730
<b>KANOMJEEN</b>

76
00:07:31,370 --> 00:07:32,040
Hello, Jeen?

77
00:07:32,050 --> 00:07:33,670
<i>Min, don't hang up!</i>

78
00:07:33,940 --> 00:07:35,720
<i>Tell me where you are now!</i>

79
00:07:36,130 --> 00:07:37,510
<i>Where I'm at is my business.</i>

80
00:07:37,960 --> 00:07:38,960
<i>It has nothing to do with you.</i>

81
00:07:39,320 --> 00:07:40,660
Stop doing this already, Min.

82
00:07:41,250 --> 00:07:42,660
<i>I'm not going to Vancouver no matter what.</i>

83
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:43,740
<i>I'll stay here.</i>

84
00:07:44,120 --> 00:07:45,400
I'll find you, Min.

85
00:07:45,960 --> 00:07:46,560
Q.

86
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:47,900
<i>I didn't run away from you.</i>

87
00:07:48,260 --> 00:07:49,800
<i>I had been selling my house for ages.</i>

88
00:07:50,060 --> 00:07:50,860
<i>After it was sold,</i>

89
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:52,470
<i>I moved out. That's it.</i>

90
00:07:53,110 --> 00:07:55,570
Whether you're going to Vancouver or staying here

91
00:07:55,940 --> 00:07:57,010
has nothing to do with me.

92
00:07:57,520 --> 00:07:59,100
<i>Stop pretending you don't care about me.</i>

93
00:08:00,270 --> 00:08:01,400
I want to be with you,

94
00:08:02,780 --> 00:08:03,960
and you want to be with me.

95
00:08:04,290 --> 00:08:05,410
<i>I don't want to be with you.</i>

96
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:07,360
<i>I told you already</i>

97
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:09,210
I wouldn't risk my brother's life anymore.

98
00:08:10,410 --> 00:08:11,900
<i>I can't risk my life either.</i>

99
00:08:12,380 --> 00:08:13,180
<i>I only have Mhen,</i>

100
00:08:13,660 --> 00:08:14,800
and Mhen only has me.

101
00:08:16,320 --> 00:08:17,770
Since I chose my family,

102
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:20,980
that means I can't have you in my life.

103
00:08:23,460 --> 00:08:25,100
Is this what you really think, Min?

104
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:30,810
Exactly.

105
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:33,520
Forget me already.

106
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:40,690
<i>I'll forget you, too.</i>

107
00:08:49,770 --> 00:08:53,410
Are Mhen and you doing fine?

108
00:08:55,150 --> 00:08:56,100
We're fine.

109
00:09:41,520 --> 00:09:44,890
<b>Q</b>

110
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,690
<b>no signal</b>

111
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:13,930
<b>THAILAND</b>
<b>PASTPORT</b>

112
00:10:42,990 --> 00:10:45,200
Mr. Q still visits Min's house often.

113
00:10:45,830 --> 00:10:48,570
Do you want me to announce the sale now, Mr. Kacha?

114
00:10:49,690 --> 00:10:51,800
Otherwise, it'll be pointless to have them move out.

115
00:10:53,770 --> 00:10:55,100
You ordered Min to do this, right?!

116
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:57,100
What did you say to him?!

117
00:10:57,120 --> 00:10:58,790
I think you'd better calm down.

118
00:10:58,800 --> 00:11:00,020
Where is Min now?!

119
00:11:07,720 --> 00:11:10,060
<i>Now, Min is at his old house in Chonburi.</i>

120
00:11:14,420 --> 00:11:15,260
Give me a second.

121
00:11:48,480 --> 00:11:49,860
Q is with me now, Suea,

122
00:11:50,370 --> 00:11:52,100
but it's already late, so he has to sleep over.

123
00:11:52,530 --> 00:11:54,170
In the morning, I'll let him leave.

124
00:11:55,610 --> 00:11:56,320
Sure.

125
00:11:58,620 --> 00:11:59,710
Who told you I'm heading back?

126
00:11:59,820 --> 00:12:01,200
And who told you I'm letting you stay?

127
00:12:04,110 --> 00:12:04,960
I've already found out that

128
00:12:05,400 --> 00:12:06,740
my dad forced you to stay here.

129
00:12:07,150 --> 00:12:08,100
Stop acting cool already.

130
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:12,850
I told you nobody forced me to do anything.

131
00:12:13,030 --> 00:12:15,200
- I made my own decision.
- Don't say that.

132
00:12:15,430 --> 00:12:16,300
I won't believe it anyway.

133
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:16,980
Well said.

134
00:12:23,270 --> 00:12:25,960
You can stay here, but only for tonight.

135
00:12:26,290 --> 00:12:27,710
After you wake up tomorrow, head back.

136
00:12:27,730 --> 00:12:28,460
I don't know.

137
00:12:28,710 --> 00:12:30,210
We'll see. It depends on my mood.

138
00:12:30,531 --> 00:12:31,000
Q.

139
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:32,410
Ouch, Min.

140
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,100
What happened to your arm again?

141
00:12:36,610 --> 00:12:38,250
I climbed your house in Bangkok.

142
00:12:38,260 --> 00:12:40,730
I told you already not to go back there again.

143
00:12:40,750 --> 00:12:41,970
Stop arguing already.

144
00:12:42,730 --> 00:12:43,550
Let's go to bed.

145
00:12:43,640 --> 00:12:44,430
I'm already sleepy,

146
00:12:44,760 --> 00:12:46,320
but let's bring a blanket to lie down here.

147
00:12:47,530 --> 00:12:48,980
I don't want you to sleep alone, Q.

148
00:12:49,450 --> 00:12:50,510
This house has a scary ghost.

149
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:53,340
At night,

150
00:12:53,900 --> 00:12:55,860
I hear crying sounds every night,

151
00:12:56,170 --> 00:12:59,420
like 'hoo hoo hoo.'

152
00:12:59,780 --> 00:13:00,900
Just talking about it gives me chills.

153
00:13:03,190 --> 00:13:05,340
Hoo, hoo.

154
00:13:18,770 --> 00:13:19,822
He thinks he looks that cute, huh?

155
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:26,510
Mhen.

156
00:13:26,770 --> 00:13:27,300
Yeah?

157
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:29,100
I'm sorry

158
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:32,200
for being the reason that put you in trouble.

159
00:13:32,500 --> 00:13:33,570
Don't worry at all.

160
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,060
You don't have to say sorry.

161
00:13:35,370 --> 00:13:36,700
You saved me.

162
00:13:37,130 --> 00:13:38,410
I should thank you.

163
00:13:39,110 --> 00:13:40,619
But if you just lived your normal life,

164
00:13:41,440 --> 00:13:43,349
you wouldn't have to face such a thing from the start.

165
00:13:43,361 --> 00:13:44,019
Am I right?

166
00:13:46,750 --> 00:13:50,268
You aren't supposed to face
something terrible like this, either.

167
00:13:50,770 --> 00:13:54,610
But I understand that
it's something you've been born with.

168
00:13:55,000 --> 00:13:56,110
It can't be fixed.

169
00:13:57,580 --> 00:13:58,560
Take me as an example.

170
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:03,465
I can't do anything about this
apart from living with it as happy as I can.

171
00:14:07,320 --> 00:14:08,710
You're this cute.

172
00:14:09,410 --> 00:14:10,970
That's why Min loves you so dearly.

173
00:14:12,330 --> 00:14:13,570
Let's sleep.

174
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:15,011
You're gossiping about me, huh?

175
00:14:16,340 --> 00:14:17,040
No.

176
00:14:18,430 --> 00:14:19,200
Let's sleep, Mhen.

177
00:14:20,150 --> 00:14:21,300
Mhen, move. I'll sleep here, too.

178
00:14:29,350 --> 00:14:30,020
Turn off the light.

179
00:14:42,520 --> 00:14:43,130
Let's sleep.

180
00:15:14,070 --> 00:15:15,560
Did you really use the same soap as us?

181
00:15:16,028 --> 00:15:17,010
Why does your body smell so good?

182
00:15:17,030 --> 00:15:17,970
It doesn't smell the same.

183
00:15:19,060 --> 00:15:20,430
- It isn't?
- Yeah.

184
00:15:20,450 --> 00:15:22,000
I used that one in the bathroom.

185
00:15:23,450 --> 00:15:24,050
You did?

186
00:15:28,330 --> 00:15:29,260
What's with you?

187
00:15:29,540 --> 00:15:30,510
I'm attached to the bolster.

188
00:15:30,780 --> 00:15:31,990
Your bedroom doesn't even have one.

189
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:33,120
Be quiet. I'll sleep.

190
00:15:34,590 --> 00:15:35,220
Let's sleep.

191
00:17:25,110 --> 00:17:25,660
Q.

192
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:27,850
Q, you're sleepwalking.

193
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:31,225
You're heading toward the wall.
You might bump into it.

194
00:17:33,370 --> 00:17:34,210
Let's go back to sleep.

195
00:18:01,960 --> 00:18:02,890
I'm sorry.

196
00:18:03,810 --> 00:18:04,860
I broke our promise.

197
00:19:06,150 --> 00:19:06,770
Min!

198
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:08,900
My car's broken.

199
00:19:09,300 --> 00:19:10,110
I can't go back anymore.

200
00:19:16,250 --> 00:19:17,220
Hello, mechanic?

201
00:19:17,950 --> 00:19:19,500
There's a car broken in front of my house.

202
00:19:19,510 --> 00:19:21,170
Can you come check it out now, please?

203
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,230
Okay. Thank you so much.

204
00:19:28,390 --> 00:19:29,200
After your car is fixed,

205
00:19:29,410 --> 00:19:30,010
you must head back.

206
00:19:30,200 --> 00:19:30,820
I don't know.

207
00:19:31,090 --> 00:19:32,251
- We'll see.
- Q.

208
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:34,400
I'm being serious here.

209
00:19:36,150 --> 00:19:37,370
How many times do I have to say this?

210
00:19:37,540 --> 00:19:38,660
You can't stay here.

211
00:19:38,810 --> 00:19:39,670
You must head back.

212
00:19:39,690 --> 00:19:40,950
Why must I?

213
00:19:41,460 --> 00:19:44,010
Yada and her men have already escaped overseas.

214
00:19:44,080 --> 00:19:45,400
My dad isn't handling a new case, either.

215
00:19:45,890 --> 00:19:47,160
If you make me go back now,

216
00:19:48,230 --> 00:19:50,170
it's like you're breaking up
with me for free. Don't you know?

217
00:19:50,570 --> 00:19:51,420
Don't you regret it?

218
00:19:55,790 --> 00:19:57,008
After your car is fixed, you must head back.

219
00:19:59,790 --> 00:20:00,570
Fine.

220
00:20:00,970 --> 00:20:02,160
Alright.

221
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:03,850
But while we're waiting,

222
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:06,742
how about going on a trip?

223
00:20:07,450 --> 00:20:08,705
What attractions do we have here in Chonburi?

224
00:20:08,742 --> 00:20:09,565
Show me around.

225
00:20:09,980 --> 00:20:10,670
A trip?

226
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:12,110
I don't have time for that.

227
00:20:12,590 --> 00:20:13,410
I have to work.

228
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:14,900
Just take Q to work with you.

229
00:20:15,870 --> 00:20:17,410
You usually take me with you, don't you?

230
00:20:37,940 --> 00:20:38,520
Hey, Min.

231
00:20:39,100 --> 00:20:40,160
What job are you doing?

232
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:41,160
What do you think?

233
00:20:41,400 --> 00:20:42,210
It's a surf shop.

234
00:20:42,920 --> 00:20:44,610
I teach customers to surf, and I'm also a staff here.

235
00:20:44,790 --> 00:20:46,410
Go buy a drink and sit to wait for me.

236
00:20:46,570 --> 00:20:47,708
I don't want to trouble the shop owner.

237
00:20:49,940 --> 00:20:50,610
That's cool.

238
00:20:51,970 --> 00:20:53,405
Well, hi.

239
00:20:53,470 --> 00:20:54,110
Oh, hi.

240
00:20:54,494 --> 00:20:56,800
Excuse me. Can you help me with surfing?

241
00:20:56,810 --> 00:20:57,650
Oh, sure.

242
00:20:57,830 --> 00:20:58,800
- Let's go.
- Okay.

243
00:20:59,350 --> 00:20:59,970
Thank you.

244
00:21:05,050 --> 00:21:05,550
Right?

245
00:21:05,610 --> 00:21:06,100
Right.

246
00:21:06,140 --> 00:21:06,770
Like this?

247
00:21:06,780 --> 00:21:07,430
Yes.

248
00:21:07,450 --> 00:21:08,000
Okay.

249
00:21:08,410 --> 00:21:09,610
Do this for ten seconds.

250
00:21:09,620 --> 00:21:10,720
Are you Min's friend?

251
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:11,810
Yes.

252
00:21:11,850 --> 00:21:12,470
Thank you.

253
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:15,960
By the way, how is Min?

254
00:21:17,070 --> 00:21:18,570
He's hard-working and determined.

255
00:21:18,890 --> 00:21:20,700
He's gaining more customers.

256
00:21:20,720 --> 00:21:22,912
As you know, he's handsome and caring.

257
00:21:22,958 --> 00:21:23,960
Any customer who came here liked him.

258
00:21:24,730 --> 00:21:25,300
Enjoy.

259
00:21:25,310 --> 00:21:27,592
Okay. Next is Dynamic Stretching.

260
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:28,245
Right, okay.

261
00:21:28,260 --> 00:21:29,370
So, how do I do this?

262
00:21:29,370 --> 00:21:30,310
You have to run.

263
00:21:31,150 --> 00:21:32,010
On the?

264
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:32,950
Yeah. Like this.

265
00:21:33,080 --> 00:21:34,010
Thirty seconds.

266
00:21:34,030 --> 00:21:34,540
Right.

267
00:21:37,940 --> 00:21:38,570
Okay.

268
00:21:38,660 --> 00:21:42,008
And next, you have to stretch like this.

269
00:21:44,860 --> 00:21:45,720
Let's go!

270
00:21:46,237 --> 00:21:47,220
I'm so excited.

271
00:21:47,230 --> 00:21:50,260
We have to learn how to stand on the board.

272
00:21:52,240 --> 00:21:54,120
Min, wait for me!

273
00:21:54,290 --> 00:21:55,000
I'm joining you.

274
00:21:57,280 --> 00:21:58,010
Let me talk to a friend.

275
00:21:58,020 --> 00:21:58,610
Okay.

276
00:22:01,210 --> 00:22:02,060
Teach me, too.

