00:22:02,490 --> 00:22:03,640
I'm also your customer.

278
00:22:03,800 --> 00:22:04,890
But you don't have any basic skills.

279
00:22:04,900 --> 00:22:05,832
You can't get in the water.

280
00:22:05,842 --> 00:22:06,670
You could get hurt.

281
00:22:06,690 --> 00:22:07,400
I know

282
00:22:08,220 --> 00:22:09,910
- you will never let me get hurt.
- Q.

283
00:22:19,920 --> 00:22:22,000
Okay, and first, we have to…

284
00:22:22,150 --> 00:22:22,760
Ouch!

285
00:22:24,310 --> 00:22:25,666
Hey, Q!

286
00:22:25,703 --> 00:22:26,370
Ouch!

287
00:22:31,670 --> 00:22:32,860
See? I told you.

288
00:22:52,010 --> 00:22:54,600
Can't you just let me live
a relaxing life for just a day?

289
00:22:54,960 --> 00:22:56,650
Working already tires me off.

290
00:22:57,460 --> 00:22:58,240
But just now,

291
00:22:59,440 --> 00:23:00,800
I didn't mean it to happen.

292
00:23:02,600 --> 00:23:04,250
I had to ask for permission to leave early today.

293
00:23:05,840 --> 00:23:06,360
Get up.

294
00:23:06,530 --> 00:23:07,110
Let's head back.

295
00:23:22,970 --> 00:23:23,560
Q.

296
00:23:27,390 --> 00:23:28,010
Q!

297
00:23:29,260 --> 00:23:30,100
Thank you.

298
00:23:30,840 --> 00:23:31,470
Q!

299
00:23:32,860 --> 00:23:33,570
Ouch!

300
00:23:34,340 --> 00:23:35,830
Why are you walking now?

301
00:23:35,850 --> 00:23:38,020
You have a wound. Sands might get into it.

302
00:23:38,260 --> 00:23:40,205
Your foot is injured,
and you're still stopping by everywhere.

303
00:23:41,750 --> 00:23:42,860
I see that you're tired,

304
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:44,350
so I grabbed something refreshing for you.

305
00:23:44,790 --> 00:23:45,420
Just drink it.

306
00:23:46,670 --> 00:23:47,940
Are you sure you won't drink it?

307
00:23:48,620 --> 00:23:51,360
Little Q even bought this for Phi Min.

308
00:23:51,950 --> 00:23:52,600
Drink a little,

309
00:23:52,990 --> 00:23:53,970
so you won't feel hot.

310
00:23:54,640 --> 00:23:55,580
Please, Phi Min.

311
00:23:56,640 --> 00:23:57,710
Phi Min.

312
00:23:57,850 --> 00:23:59,000
Drink some, Phi Min.

313
00:23:59,280 --> 00:23:59,920
Drink some.

314
00:24:14,700 --> 00:24:15,450
You're smiling now.

315
00:24:15,980 --> 00:24:16,660
I'm not.

316
00:24:17,540 --> 00:24:18,343
It just feels refreshing.

317
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:19,410
Let's head back already.

318
00:24:20,720 --> 00:24:21,650
Wait for me, Min.

319
00:24:22,710 --> 00:24:23,420
Ouch!

320
00:24:28,810 --> 00:24:29,400
Take it.

321
00:24:30,740 --> 00:24:31,410
Get on.

322
00:24:39,880 --> 00:24:41,300
You always make me worry about you.

323
00:24:44,690 --> 00:24:46,770
Hey, that's mine.

324
00:24:47,610 --> 00:24:49,520
What? I haven't drunk it.

325
00:24:53,161 --> 00:24:53,860
You want it this way, right?

326
00:24:53,880 --> 00:24:55,010
Alright. I'm giving in.

327
00:24:55,640 --> 00:24:57,030
Drink it then, Phi Min.

328
00:25:02,630 --> 00:25:03,680
Happy now?

329
00:25:07,900 --> 00:25:09,540
Why didn't you go to Vancouver then?

330
00:25:11,120 --> 00:25:13,170
Do you remember the day we filmed that zombie MV?

331
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:14,000
Yeah.

332
00:25:14,720 --> 00:25:16,610
I thought of what you said.

333
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:20,210
You told me to run away
if you ever turned into a zombie.

334
00:25:21,350 --> 00:25:25,810
So, I thought you must be doing such a thing.

335
00:25:27,620 --> 00:25:28,810
You protected me,

336
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:31,010
wanting me to be safe.

337
00:25:31,750 --> 00:25:34,560
You did everything to make me go to Vancouver.

338
00:25:36,970 --> 00:25:38,010
But if you go there,

339
00:25:38,960 --> 00:25:39,820
you'll be safe.

340
00:25:39,840 --> 00:25:40,660
For what, Min?

341
00:25:42,670 --> 00:25:44,210
To be safe but alone?

342
00:25:46,480 --> 00:25:47,410
Previously,

343
00:25:48,840 --> 00:25:50,210
I felt like I was just living a life.

344
00:25:51,720 --> 00:25:52,670
I had nothing.

345
00:25:54,670 --> 00:25:56,309
Though I was lonely,
I didn't dare to open up to anyone.

346
00:25:57,850 --> 00:25:59,510
I had a nightmare every night.

347
00:26:02,140 --> 00:26:05,000
All I could do was cry by myself.

348
00:26:07,010 --> 00:26:07,800
You know what?

349
00:26:09,270 --> 00:26:13,533
I just remembered what happiness feels like
now that I'm with you, Min.

350
00:26:20,550 --> 00:26:23,510
I'm sorry for being selfish,

351
00:26:25,480 --> 00:26:26,890
but I want to be with you, Min.

352
00:26:31,550 --> 00:26:32,460
In the end,

353
00:26:34,780 --> 00:26:38,718
I turned out to be the troublemaker.

354
00:26:39,720 --> 00:26:40,765
I've become a zombie.

355
00:26:42,310 --> 00:26:45,200
Now that I'm a zombie,

356
00:26:46,620 --> 00:26:47,720
will you shoot me

357
00:26:49,190 --> 00:26:50,210
or let me bite you?

358
00:26:54,510 --> 00:26:55,240
You'll see.

359
00:27:37,860 --> 00:27:38,600
Q, Min.

360
00:27:39,500 --> 00:27:40,460
They've done fixing the car.

361
00:27:43,790 --> 00:27:44,750
Your leg is hurt, isn't it?

362
00:27:45,410 --> 00:27:46,210
You can't drive.

363
00:27:46,810 --> 00:27:47,700
Stay here one more night.

364
00:27:53,230 --> 00:27:54,170
Is he angry about something?

365
00:28:05,570 --> 00:28:06,160
Min!

366
00:28:06,970 --> 00:28:07,570
Mhen!

367
00:28:08,890 --> 00:28:09,470
Min!

368
00:28:09,930 --> 00:28:10,500
Mhen!

369
00:28:18,220 --> 00:28:18,920
Hey, Q?

370
00:28:19,670 --> 00:28:20,320
You're up already?

371
00:28:24,400 --> 00:28:25,410
By the way,

372
00:28:26,040 --> 00:28:27,660
this red wolf suits you well.

373
00:28:30,970 --> 00:28:31,700
Well,

374
00:28:32,540 --> 00:28:33,800
Min allowed you to ride a motorcycle already?

375
00:28:34,770 --> 00:28:35,310
Yeah,

376
00:28:35,580 --> 00:28:36,936
only when I have to go out to buy food.

377
00:28:37,450 --> 00:28:39,917
Also, I lived here when I was a kid.

378
00:28:39,937 --> 00:28:40,874
Everyone here knows each other.

379
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:41,810
That's why Min allowed me to.

380
00:28:43,730 --> 00:28:44,740
Where is Min now?

381
00:28:45,210 --> 00:28:47,000
He works as a trainer at the gym.

382
00:28:48,430 --> 00:28:49,710
By the way,

383
00:28:50,050 --> 00:28:51,870
Min asked you to take a shower and get dressed.

384
00:28:52,180 --> 00:28:53,040
He'll take us on a trip.

385
00:28:53,120 --> 00:28:53,720
A trip?

386
00:28:54,240 --> 00:28:54,890
Where?

387
00:28:55,180 --> 00:28:56,700
If I tell you, it's not going to be a surprise.

388
00:28:57,290 --> 00:28:58,010
Let's eat.

389
00:28:58,370 --> 00:28:59,020
I'm hungry.

390
00:29:09,430 --> 00:29:11,400
So, where is Min taking us?

391
00:29:12,030 --> 00:29:12,760
I won't tell you.

392
00:29:13,100 --> 00:29:13,810
You'll find out soon.

393
00:29:24,100 --> 00:29:25,000
Whose car is that?

394
00:29:25,710 --> 00:29:27,060
I borrowed it from the surf shop's owner.

395
00:29:27,300 --> 00:29:28,260
Why don't we just use my car?

396
00:29:28,520 --> 00:29:29,910
Your car only fits two people.

397
00:29:30,040 --> 00:29:31,870
There are three of us here. How can we use your car?

398
00:29:32,040 --> 00:29:33,100
What are you looking at? Let's get moving.

399
00:29:33,110 --> 00:29:33,620
Now.

400
00:29:34,040 --> 00:29:34,770
Hold on.

401
00:29:35,870 --> 00:29:36,660
Do I look handsome today?

402
00:29:38,340 --> 00:29:39,020
Yeah.

403
00:29:39,340 --> 00:29:40,210
You're already handsome.

404
00:29:40,660 --> 00:29:41,300
Let's go now.

405
00:29:42,000 --> 00:29:42,610
Let's go, Mhen.

406
00:30:25,500 --> 00:30:26,100
How was today?

407
00:30:26,330 --> 00:30:27,170
Did you enjoy it?

408
00:30:28,090 --> 00:30:28,720
I did.

409
00:30:29,920 --> 00:30:31,222
What were you thinking bringing me here?

410
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:35,040
I wanted to apologize for leaving you.

411
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:38,500
You already did that on the first night I arrived.

412
00:30:39,380 --> 00:30:39,930
Huh?

413
00:30:40,490 --> 00:30:41,200
Yeah.

414
00:30:41,810 --> 00:30:43,010
I didn't sleepwalk that night.

415
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:48,408
So, was that what you did
every time I sleepwalked at night?

416
00:30:50,420 --> 00:30:51,100
Nope.

417
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:53,604
I just followed what the website suggested.

418
00:30:53,670 --> 00:30:55,550
I did what it said.

419
00:30:58,420 --> 00:31:03,310
So, did I look silly pretending
to play it cool with you?

420
00:31:03,390 --> 00:31:04,500
No, you didn't.

421
00:31:06,600 --> 00:31:09,600
I'm glad to know that you still love me.

422
00:31:09,620 --> 00:31:10,840
Did I ever say I love you?

423
00:31:10,860 --> 00:31:11,750
Then say it.

424
00:31:17,380 --> 00:31:21,170
I've got the answer
to your question from yesterday.

425
00:31:23,700 --> 00:31:28,830
You asked if I'd shoot you or let you bite me
if you turned into a zombie.

426
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:33,970
<b>Q</b>

427
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:16,210
So,

428
00:32:17,100 --> 00:32:19,900
when are Min and you moving back to Bangkok?

429
00:32:20,440 --> 00:32:23,160
Min said we moved here for good.

430
00:32:23,780 --> 00:32:25,260
He wanted me to continue my study here.

431
00:32:26,770 --> 00:32:30,610
But he made that decision then because of you.

432
00:32:31,070 --> 00:32:32,370
I'm not sure...

433
00:32:32,940 --> 00:32:34,000
if he has changed his mind already.

434
00:32:35,070 --> 00:32:36,810
If you really have to live here,

435
00:32:38,340 --> 00:32:39,810
won't you miss Kanomjeen?

436
00:32:42,380 --> 00:32:43,460
Actually...

437
00:32:44,320 --> 00:32:46,310
I already asked her to study here with me.

438
00:32:49,060 --> 00:32:51,540
Snacks and food are here!

439
00:32:51,650 --> 00:32:52,810
I'll go grab some drinks.

440
00:32:54,210 --> 00:32:55,000
It's alright, Mhen.

441
00:32:55,390 --> 00:32:56,530
I'm going to the toilet.

442
00:33:00,390 --> 00:33:02,060
Won't you ask a bit where Mhen is going?

443
00:33:03,240 --> 00:33:04,300
Maybe he's just grabbing some snacks.

444
00:33:04,810 --> 00:33:06,210
You've been less strict with Mhen these days.

445
00:33:06,680 --> 00:33:07,520
Come on.

446
00:33:08,060 --> 00:33:09,980
You used to blame me for being protective of him.

447
00:33:10,020 --> 00:33:11,130
It's good you're doing this.

448
00:33:11,890 --> 00:33:12,560
Look at Mhen.

449
00:33:12,980 --> 00:33:14,210
He seems a lot more lively.

450
00:33:15,850 --> 00:33:17,200
I guess it's because he has things to do.

451
00:33:17,660 --> 00:33:19,910
When he's bored, he just chills at the beach.

452
00:33:20,370 --> 00:33:21,714
There's a market down the street from our place.

453
00:33:22,020 --> 00:33:22,790
You know what?

454
00:33:22,810 --> 00:33:24,370
You taught him to ride a motorcycle, right?

455
00:33:24,580 --> 00:33:29,210
Now it's less than 10 meters from our house
to the street with the food shop,

456
00:33:29,300 --> 00:33:30,800
and he rides his motorcycle there.

457
00:33:34,040 --> 00:33:34,910
Is something wrong?

458
00:33:36,060 --> 00:33:36,700
No.

459
00:33:37,510 --> 00:33:39,601
I'm just feeling a bit of pain around my wound.

460
00:33:42,080 --> 00:33:43,820
Hey, it's alright.

461
00:33:44,630 --> 00:33:45,700
It's normal.

462
00:33:46,050 --> 00:33:47,460
The wound isn't healed yet,

463
00:33:48,010 --> 00:33:48,960
and I've been walking a lot.

464
00:33:50,010 --> 00:33:51,420
Whoa.

465
00:33:51,700 --> 00:33:53,640
The sea is very sweet.

466
00:33:54,470 --> 00:33:55,300
Who told you to tease me?

467
00:33:55,410 --> 00:33:56,417
It's worth teasing, isn't it?

468
00:33:56,460 --> 00:33:57,410
Yesterday, you chased him away.

469
00:33:57,750 --> 00:34:00,600
Today, you asked, “Is your wound hurt, darling, my baby?”

470
00:34:00,730 --> 00:34:02,594
Baby? Nonsense. I never said that.

471
00:34:02,910 --> 00:34:04,272
Come here. Come here. Come here now!

472
00:34:08,161 --> 00:34:09,312
What should you do
when running after your brother?

473
00:34:11,720 --> 00:34:12,570
You're cheating.

474
00:34:13,820 --> 00:34:14,530
Here you go.

475
00:34:19,240 --> 00:34:20,250
I can't keep up!

476
00:34:22,280 --> 00:34:22,830
Hey!

477
00:34:23,260 --> 00:34:23,820
Q!

478
00:34:33,430 --> 00:34:34,410
Q!

479
00:34:34,650 --> 00:34:35,360
It's over.

480
00:34:36,860 --> 00:34:38,210
It's over.

481
00:34:38,370 --> 00:34:39,220
Q, it's over.

482
00:34:40,830 --> 00:34:42,050
It's alright. You're fine.

483
00:34:42,830 --> 00:34:43,710
They were just lighting firecrackers.

484
00:34:44,940 --> 00:34:45,910
Everything is alright now. It's over.

485
00:35:11,440 --> 00:35:12,670
I'll head to my room and sleep, Min.

486
00:35:15,180 --> 00:35:16,310
How about we sleep upstairs tonight?

487
00:35:19,810 --> 00:35:20,533
No, Min.

488
00:35:20,832 --> 00:35:22,820
I think I should head back now.

489
00:35:23,150 --> 00:35:24,110
Why?

490
00:35:25,130 --> 00:35:26,960
It's already late. Why not head back tomorrow?

491
00:35:27,330 --> 00:35:28,760
Driving at night is dangerous.

492
00:35:29,540 --> 00:35:30,260
It's fine.

493
00:35:30,770 --> 00:35:32,760
I think I should head back now.

494
00:35:43,340 --> 00:35:43,920
But...

495
00:35:44,990 --> 00:35:46,260
But you're okay, right?

496
00:35:47,690 --> 00:35:49,820
Or do you have work early tomorrow?

497
00:35:51,740 --> 00:35:55,480
Min, I've changed my mind.

498
00:35:56,390 --> 00:35:57,100
I think...

499
00:35:58,970 --> 00:36:00,160
I'll go to Vancouver.

500
00:36:05,970 --> 00:36:06,900
What do you mean?

501
00:36:08,310 --> 00:36:12,520
At first, I came here because I thought
my dad forced you to make this decision.

502
00:36:13,760 --> 00:36:14,410
But now,

503
00:36:15,490 --> 00:36:21,520
I can see that you and Mhen are better off
than when you were in Bangkok.

504
00:36:22,420 --> 00:36:23,670
You have your own way of life.

505
00:36:24,720 --> 00:36:25,610
<i>You're already handsome.</i>

506
00:36:26,260 --> 00:36:27,770
Mhen is also really happy.

507
00:36:29,830 --> 00:36:30,500
<i>You're up already?</i>

508
00:36:31,440 --> 00:36:32,570
What you said is true.

509
00:36:34,530 --> 00:36:38,470
We shouldn't risk someone else's life like this.

510
00:36:38,940 --> 00:36:39,660
Hey, Q.

511
00:36:40,340 --> 00:36:41,760
But back then,

512
00:36:42,780 --> 00:36:44,801
I said that because I wanted you
to be somewhere safe.

513
00:36:46,750 --> 00:36:49,420
- I didn't mean it like that.
- But it's true, Min.

514
00:36:52,420 --> 00:36:53,700
You also know it's true.

515
00:36:58,110 --> 00:37:00,020
But you told me you wouldn't run away again.

516
00:37:00,090 --> 00:37:01,100
I lied.

517
00:37:02,280 --> 00:37:05,210
Someone like me will always face this.

518
00:37:07,130 --> 00:37:07,860
I think...

519
00:37:08,810 --> 00:37:10,110
it's best for me to be alone.

520
00:37:11,020 --> 00:37:11,700
Nope.

521
00:37:12,830 --> 00:37:14,720
- I don't think that at all.
- Min.

522
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:16,920
Earlier today,

523
00:37:17,600 --> 00:37:19,010
when Mhen heard the firecrackers,

524
00:37:19,670 --> 00:37:22,310
he started to fear them just like I do.

525
00:37:24,590 --> 00:37:25,140
<i>Hey!</i>

526
00:37:25,500 --> 00:37:26,010
<i>Q!</i>

527
00:37:30,320 --> 00:37:31,010
See?

528
00:37:32,950 --> 00:37:39,140
It's not worth it at all risking our loved
one's life for our own happiness.

529
00:37:41,200 --> 00:37:41,860
So...

530
00:37:42,440 --> 00:37:43,420
So what now?

531
00:37:44,170 --> 00:37:46,370
Do you want me to let you go back to your old life?

532
00:37:48,320 --> 00:37:50,800
Like you told me you were just living day by day?

533
00:37:52,950 --> 00:37:54,800
Parting while alive is
better than parting in death.

534
00:37:57,980 --> 00:38:02,000
I think if we stay knowing that...

535
00:38:03,380 --> 00:38:04,820
one day we loved each other so much,

536
00:38:05,810 --> 00:38:11,170
and right now you're somewhere happy and safe,

537
00:38:12,170 --> 00:38:13,310
it's really not that bad.

538
00:38:19,610 --> 00:38:20,610
Are you really leaving?

539
00:38:22,440 --> 00:38:28,470
Go back and choose Mhen's life like you always did.

540
00:38:30,660 --> 00:38:31,620
As for me,

541
00:38:32,590 --> 00:38:34,160
I'll just go back and live alone, like before.

542
00:38:36,480 --> 00:38:37,810
Please say goodbye to Mhen for me.

543
00:38:42,050 --> 00:38:45,600
Be really happy, okay?

544
00:38:47,210 --> 00:38:48,760
Think that you're doing it for me.

545
00:38:54,830 --> 00:38:55,560
Let go of me.

546
00:39:00,100 --> 00:39:00,730
Q.

547
00:39:00,800 --> 00:39:01,410
Q.

548
00:40:15,470 --> 00:40:15,940
No.

549
00:40:15,960 --> 00:40:16,620
Q. Q!

550
00:40:28,840 --> 00:40:29,410
Q!

551
00:40:37,330 --> 00:40:38,010
Q!

552
00:40:40,260 --> 00:40:41,160
Q!

553
00:40:44,110 --> 00:40:45,120
Q, pull over!

554
00:40:46,190 --> 00:40:46,930
Pull over!

555
00:40:58,600 --> 00:40:59,210
Q.

556
00:40:59,710 --> 00:41:00,500
Q, open the door.

557
00:41:00,680 --> 00:41:01,340
